summary: An Ordinance repealing Ordinance No. 11467, entitled "An Ordinance providing for the improvement of Taylor Avenue, in the City of Seattle, from a point one hundred twenty (120) feet south of Aloha Street to Republican Street, by constructing a sewer therein of proper dimensions, together with all necessary manholes, wyes, catch basins, lampholes, and other appurtenances, in accordance with Resolution No. 236 of the City Council of the City of Seattle, and providing for the payment therefor by the mode of "Immediate Payment," under the provisions of Ordinance No. 5693 of said city, approved December 6, 1899."
